value.title: Trump tweets from hospital as doc confirms Remdesivir treatment: ‘Going well, I think!’
value.excerpt: President Trump posted a Twitter message from Walter Reed Medical Center on Friday night, suggesting he’s feeling OK after being admitted earlier after his coronavirus diagnosis.

value.title: Sanders to host socially distant rally for Biden in New Hampshire
value.excerpt: Bernie Sanders will hold a socially distanced rally for Democratic nominee Joe Biden in New Hampshire on Saturday, the Biden campaign announced.

value.title: Trump team thinks Nevada is in play. Is it?
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign has been hitting Nevada harder than ever this election season, and they seem certain the state might be President Trump’s for the taking this November.

value.title: Trump’s campaign ‘may be more focused and disciplined’ without in-person events: Karl Rove
value.excerpt: President Trump being forced to hold virtual campaign events after testing positive for coronavirus may cause him to be more "focused and disciplined" in his messaging, Fox News contributor Karl Rove suggested on Friday.

value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.

value.title: No one wore a mask during Trump debate prep, Chris Christie says
value.excerpt: Former N.J. Gov. Chris Christie revealed that no one in the room was wearing a mask when a small group of people gathered in the White House's map room on Monday to help prep President Trump for the first debate.

value.title: Boris Johnson wishes Trump 'speedy recovery' from COVID-19
value.excerpt: UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson wished President Trump a "speedy recovery" Friday, hours after he and First Lady Melania Trump tested positive for COVID-19.

value.title: Trump pledges to overturn Navy SEAL gender-neutral ethos, calls it 'ridiculous'
value.excerpt: “Man” and “brotherhood” were replaced with gender-neutral phrases such as “warrior” and “group of maritime warriors.”

value.title: Cruz slams Biden for dodging court-packing questions, claims ex-VP 'doesn't want to be honest' with Americans
value.excerpt: Joe Biden does not possess the strength to stand up to the "rage and fury" of the far left as evidenced by his refusal to say whether he supports expanding the Supreme Court if elected, Sen. Ted Cruz, R-Texas, told "The Story" Thursday.

value.title: Herschel Walker claps back at Biden's Antifa is ‘an idea’ comment
value.excerpt: Former NFL star Herschel Walker turned to Twitter Thursday to take issue with a Trump-Biden debate moment regarding far-left and far-right groups and the roles they play in unrest that has rocked cities across the country.

value.title: Comey 'blatantly accused' Trump of 'horrible things' without evidence: Sen. Mike Lee
value.excerpt: Former FBI Director James Comey “blatantly accused the president of the United States” of “horrible things without any evidence,” Sen. Mike Lee, R-Utah, told “Fox & Friends” on Thursday.

value.title: Biden endorsed by more than 120 former GOP national security officials
value.excerpt: More than 120 former GOP national security officials endorsed Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden on Thursday, joining a cadre of Republican groups to oppose the reelection of President Trump.

value.title: Hillary Clinton: Trump shows his ‘first allegiance is not to the United States of America’
value.excerpt: Former Democratic presidential nominee Hillary Clinton on Thursday reiterated allegations that called into question President Donald Trump’s loyalty to the United States.

value.title: Pelosi warns Trump 'ain't no light at the end of the tunnel' should election be decided in House
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi spelled out a dire prediction for President Trump should the election come down to the House to be decided.

value.title: Biden-Schumer-Pelosi would do more damage in 2 years than Obama did in 8: Ted Cruz
value.excerpt: A “Biden-Schumer-Pelosi government” would be a “nightmare,” Sen. Ted Cruz, R-Texas, said on Thursday as he encouraged Republicans to vote in the upcoming elections.

value.title: Chaffetz rips mainstream media hypocrisy on Hunter Biden: Shame on them
value.excerpt: The mainstream media's treatment of Joe Biden and his son, Hunter Biden, is a "national embarrassment" compared to how President Trump and his family are treated, Fox News contributor Jason Chaffetz told "Fox & Friends" Thursday.

value.title: Biden calls first debate 'embarrassing for the country,' wonders how many people took 'kids away from the television'

value.title: Biden, Mr. Rogers' widow Joanne hold virtual call during Pennsylvania campaign stop
value.excerpt: Rogers, 92, is an outspoken critic of President Trump and supporter of the Biden campaign.

value.title: Biden says at debate he doesn't support Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it 'crucial framework'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden said Tuesday night at the first presidential debate that he does not support the Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it a “crucial framework” for meeting climate change challenges.

value.title: Former Playboy Playmate Karen McDougal says she’s ‘been forgiven by Jesus’ for alleged Trump affair
value.excerpt: During the 2016 election, National Enquirer parent company American Media Inc. paid McDougal $150,000 for the rights to her story, which it never published. The company eventually acknowledged the purchase was a “catch-and-kill” maneuver to boost Trump's presidential prospects.

value.title: Florida's top city for Cuban exiles goes to bat for GOP in 2020: 'Trump Town'
value.excerpt: The city of Hialeah, outside Miami, is known for its Cuban American community of working families, tight incomes and friendships among neighbors -- and as the election nears, many say they're leaning strongly toward voting for President Trump.

value.title: CNN’s Don Lemon suggests Trump was ‘hopped up’ on performance-enhancing drugs during debate
value.excerpt: CNN’s Don Lemon suggested that President Trump appeared to be “hopped up” on a performance-enhancing drug during Tuesday night’s presidential debate.

value.title: Matt Gorman: Trump has a new running mate now
value.excerpt: Yes, Vice President Mike Pence is still around. And no, the near-constant chatter about former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley did not come to pass.

value.title: 'Borat' sequel -- with Pence name in title -- to be released before 2020 election by Amazon
value.excerpt: The 2006 original film, written and produced by Cohen, follows the titular character, a Kazakh television personality, as he explores America.

value.title: Trump campaign says president has ‘continuously denounced’ white supremacists, amid criticism
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign on Tuesday told Fox News that President Trump has “continuously denounced” white supremacists, including during the first presidential debate, when they say he did so “twice.”

value.title: Dana Perino's debate verdict: 'Biden cleared the very low bar that had been set for him'
value.excerpt: Democrats concerned about Joe Biden's performance on a debate stage could breathe a sigh of relief Tuesday night following the fractious and bad-tempered first confrontation in Cleveland, former White House press secretary Dana Perino said.

value.title: Trump on Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade: 'There's nothing happening there'
value.excerpt: President Trump said Tuesday night there’s “nothing happening” in the Supreme Court with Roe v. Wade, and it isn’t on the ballot with the latest Supreme Court vacancy.

value.title: Philly firefighters, paramedics union breaks with IAFF to endorse Trump
value.excerpt: The firefighters and paramedics union in Philadelphia broke with the International Association of Fire Fighters to endorse President Trump in the upcoming election, according to a report.

value.title: Netanyahu says Trump’s critics ‘dead wrong’ on Middle East peace efforts
value.excerpt: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Tuesday that President Trump’s critics were “dead wrong,” in predicting that the Trump administration’s attempts to bring peace to the Middle East would fail -- after a series of landmark U.S.-brokered deals were signed this month.
